                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Legal Adviser, Phleger, on January 22, 1954, addressed the Pennsylvania Bar
                    Association on recent developments in international law of interest to the
                    United States. Two sections of his address <pb facs="0907" n="1697"
                        xml:id="pg_1697"/> dealt with the activities of the International Law
                    Commission and the Continental Shelf Doctrine; see Department of State <hi
                        rend="italic">Bulletin,</hi> February 8, 1954, pages 199 and 200.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
